Blocks.childText: Watcher. 153 1 When shall the voice of singing 1 Go when the morning shineth, 1 I want to be like Jesus, Flow joyfully along? Go when the moon is bright, So lowly and SO meek; When hill and valley, ringing Go when the eve declineth, For no one marked an angry word With one triumphant song, Go in the hush of night; That ever heard him speak. Proclaim the contest ended, Go with pure mind and feeling, I want to be like Jesus, And Him who once was slain, Drive earthly thoughts away, So frequently in prayer; Again to earth descended, And, in thy closet kneeling, Alone upon the mountain-top, In righteousness to reign. Do thou in secret pray. He met his Father there. 2 Then from the craggy mountains, 2 Remember all who love thee, 2 I want to be like Jesus; The sacred shout shall fly; And who are loved by thee; I never, never find And shady vales and fountains Pray, too, for those who hate thee, That he, though persecuted, was Shall echo the reply. If any such there be; To any one unkind. High tower and lowly dwelling Then, for thyself, in meekness, I want to be like Jesus, Shall send the chorus round, A blessing humbly claim Engaged in doing good, All hallelujahs swelling, And blend with each petition So that of me it may be said, In one eternal sound! Thy great Redeemer's name. She hath done what she could." Guide. 7s. M. M. WELLS. D.C. ae 1 Holy Spirit, faithful Guide, 2 Ever present, truest friend, 3 When our days of toil shall cease, Ever near the Christian's side, Ever near, thine aid to lend, Waiting still for sweet release, Gently lead us by the hand, Leave us not to doubt and fear, Nothing left but heaven and prayer, Pilgrims in a desert land. Groping on in darkness drear. Wond'ring if our names are there; Weary souls, fore'er rejoice, When the storms are raging sore, Wading deep the dismal flood, While they hear that sweetest voice, Hearts grow faint and hopes; give o'er, Pleading naught but Jesus' blood; Whisp'ring softly, wanderer, come! Whisper softly, wanderer, come! Whisper softly, wanderer come! Follow me, I'll guide thee home. Follow me, I 11 guide thee home. Follow me, 'll guide thee home.
